<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,858,543,569]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Morphological redescription of female 
<typeStatus box="[684,738,543,569]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
material.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,357,2026]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[276,367,581,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="54.[151,255,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[216,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-45@54.[214,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 29. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): head, antenna 1, antenna 2, labrum, mandible, labium, maxilla 1, maxilla 2. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
): small and rounded, cephalic lobe acute, with a small and rounded lobe next to basis of antenna 2; eyes small, 1/3 length of head, and rounded, well defined. Antenna 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1121,1211,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="54.[151,255,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[216,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-45@54.[214,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 29. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): head, antenna 1, antenna 2, labrum, mandible, labium, maxilla 1, maxilla 2. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
): short and stocky; peduncle article 1 broader and longer than rest of peduncle, as long as article 2; flagellum 8-articulate, as long as peduncle, two simple setae apically; no accessory flagellum observed. Antenna 2 (
<figureCitation box="[1203,1296,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="54.[151,255,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[216,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-45@54.[214,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 29. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): head, antenna 1, antenna 2, labrum, mandible, labium, maxilla 1, maxilla 2. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
): broken in examined material; peduncle as long as all of antenna 1, peduncle article 4 and 5 subequal in length, all of peduncle slimmer than article one of antenna 1 peduncle. Labrum (
<figureCitation box="[931,1019,768,794]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="54.[151,255,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[216,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-45@54.[214,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 29. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): head, antenna 1, antenna 2, labrum, mandible, labium, maxilla 1, maxilla 2. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
): rounded. Mandible (
<figureCitation box="[1277,1366,768,794]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="54.[151,255,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[216,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-45@54.[214,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 29. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): head, antenna 1, antenna 2, labrum, mandible, labium, maxilla 1, maxilla 2. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
): palp missing after dissection, but is drawn on the head-drawing in 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars, G. O. &amp; The Crustacea of Norway" box="[903,1046,805,831]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref21742" refString="Sars, G. O. (1890 - 95). The Crustacea of Norway., volume 1. Amphipoda. Alb. Cammermeyers forlag. (Stenothoid part published 1892)" type="book" year="1892">Sars (1892)</bibRefCitation>
, even though no mouthparts are described in his text; incisor and lacinia mobilis crenulate but well defined; raker setae broad plates flat and serrate distally; no molar. Maxilla 1 (
<figureCitation box="[596,687,880,906]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="54.[151,255,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[216,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-45@54.[214,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 29. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): head, antenna 1, antenna 2, labrum, mandible, labium, maxilla 1, maxilla 2. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
): inner plate rounded, one simple seta apically; outer plate flat distally, one tooth, two short and three long cuspidate setae, a row of minute simple setae along inner margin; palp 1-articulate, one tooth and one largish cuspidate seta distally, serrate inner margin lined with simple setae. Maxilla 2 (
<figureCitation box="[361,452,992,1018]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="54.[151,255,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[216,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-45@54.[214,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 29. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): head, antenna 1, antenna 2, labrum, mandible, labium, maxilla 1, maxilla 2. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
): outer plate in normal position to inner plate, rounded; four and six simple setae distally respectively. Labium (
<figureCitation box="[509,598,1029,1055]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="54.[151,255,1952,1976]" captionTargetBox="[216,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-45@54.[214,1373,194,1931]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 29. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): head, antenna 1, antenna 2, labrum, mandible, labium, maxilla 1, maxilla 2. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
): pointed, lined with simple setae along inner margin. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="55.[151,257,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[229,1357,194,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-34@55.[229,1358,194,1943]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 30. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): gnathopod 1, gnathopod 2, maxilliped. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
): long and semislender; inner plates fully separate, two distal simple setae on each lobe; outer plate with a small elongation along inner margin, wider than palp; palp 4-articulate, inner margin of first two articles lined with simple setae, article 3 with a cushion of simple setae at inner distal margin, article 4 lined with simple setae along inner margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,357,2026]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Pereon: smooth. Pereopod 1 (
<figureCitation box="[544,633,1216,1242]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="55.[151,257,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[229,1357,194,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-34@55.[229,1358,194,1943]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 30. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): gnathopod 1, gnathopod 2, maxilliped. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
): subchelate; coxa subquadrate, small; basis elongate, straight, lined with simple setae along anterior margin; ischium and merus short, merus subtriangular with a cushion of short simple setae along posterior margin; carpus elongate and very narrow, 2/3 length of basis and slightly narrower, a few simple setae along posterior margin; propodus narrow and elongate, length almost 4x width, which is slightly flaring at distal margin, palm transverse, smooth, lined with a few simple setae, palmar corner set off by one cuspidate seta; dactylus as long as palm, curved, inner margin naked, three simple setae along proximal outer margin. Pereopod 2 (
<figureCitation box="[700,798,1440,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="55.[151,257,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[229,1357,194,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-34@55.[229,1358,194,1943]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 30. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): gnathopod 1, gnathopod 2, maxilliped. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
): coxa suboval; basis straight and linear; ischium subquadrate; merus subtriangular; carpus cup-shaped and subtriangular with a cushion of short simple setae at posterior margin, distal margin with longer simpler setae; propodus subrectangular, palm oblique, smooth with simple setae, palmar corner set off by a tooth and two cuspidate setae, hind margin as long as palm; dactylus as long as palm before tooth, smooth and slightly curved. Pereopod 3 (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1171,1589,1615]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="56.[151,255,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[212,1375,194,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-41@56.[212,1375,194,1940]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 31. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): pereopod 3, pereopod 4, pereopod 5, telson. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
): coxa subrectangular; basis slender and straight; meral lobe reaching 1/3 of carpal length, dactylus slim and curved, propodus 2.5x dactylus length. Pereopod 4 (
<figureCitation box="[500,590,1664,1690]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="56.[151,255,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[212,1375,194,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-41@56.[212,1375,194,1940]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 31. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): pereopod 3, pereopod 4, pereopod 5, telson. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
): coxa rounded triangular; rest of leg simple; meral lobe reaching 0.4x carpus; dactylus simple and curved, 0.5x propodus. Pereopod 5 (
<figureCitation box="[907,995,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="56.[151,255,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[212,1375,194,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-41@56.[212,1375,194,1940]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 31. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): pereopod 3, pereopod 4, pereopod 5, telson. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
): coxa subquadrate; basis slender and straight; meral lobe 0.6x carpus, two simple setae at distal margin of lobe; dactylus curved and simple, 0.4x propodus. Pereopods 6 and 7 (
<figureCitation box="[508,598,1776,1802]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[265,1282,194,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-39@57.[265,1282,194,1912]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 32. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): pereopod 6, pereopod 7, uropod 1, uropod 2, uropod 3. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
): coxae small and rounded, coxa 6 slightly elongated posteriorly; bases posteriorly expanded; meral lobes 0.6x and 0.7x carpal length, respectively; both legs with sparse setation of simple short setae mainly along anterior margin; dactyli simple and curved, both with a tiny notch at tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,357,2026]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1436,152,551]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Urosome: smooth. Epimeral plate 3: posterodistal corner acute. Uropod 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1091,1182,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[265,1282,194,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-39@57.[265,1282,194,1912]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 32. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): pereopod 6, pereopod 7, uropod 1, uropod 2, uropod 3. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
): slightly longer than uropod 2; biramous, peduncle almost 2x rami length, one simple seta at distal margin; rami slightly uneven in length, outer ramus a little shorter than inner ramus. Uropod 2 (
<figureCitation box="[928,1021,1962,1988]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[265,1282,194,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-39@57.[265,1282,194,1912]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 32. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): pereopod 6, pereopod 7, uropod 1, uropod 2, uropod 3. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
): longer than uropod 3; biramous; peduncle almost 3x rami length, one simple seta at distal margin; rami subequal, naked. Uropod 3 (
<figureCitation box="[1332,1422,2000,2026]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="57.[151,255,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[265,1282,194,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-39@57.[265,1282,194,1912]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURE 32. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): pereopod 6, pereopod 7, uropod 1, uropod 2, uropod 3. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
): uniramous; peduncle shorter and wider than ramus, with a small extension at distal margin along ramus; ramus 2-articulate, the articles subequal in length; two setae at inner margin of peduncle and two setae distally at article 1 of the ramus. Telson (
<figureCitation box="[545,634,226,252]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="56.[151,255,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[212,1375,194,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-41@56.[212,1375,194,1940]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 31. Metopa leptocarpa Sars, 1883, female, F13735 (holotype): pereopod 3, pereopod 4, pereopod 5, telson. All scale bars are 0.1 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
): rounded and tongue-shaped, rather broad with length less than 2x width, naked.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,152,551]" box="[198,813,301,327]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
