<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,152,551]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,487,513]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very easily distinguishable from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boeck" authorityYear="1871" box="[974,1063,488,513]" class="Malacostraca" family="Stenothoidae" genus="Metopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[974,1063,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Metopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the very elongate carpus of gnathopod 1, and to some degree also by the long peduncles of uropods 1 and 2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
